## What This Does

Monitors CPU usage on a local Ubuntu VM (VirtualBox). When CPU exceeds **70%**, it automatically launches a new **e2-micro** instance on GCP and deploys a sample Flask web application on it.

---

## Architecture

```
Local Ubuntu VM (VirtualBox)
        |
        | monitor.py reads CPU every 5s
        |
        | CPU > 70% detected
        |
        | gcloud compute instances create
        |
        v
GCP Compute Engine (e2-micro)
        |
        | startup script runs automatically
        |
        v
Sample Flask App (port 80)
http://<external-ip>
```

