## Setup Instructions

### Step 1: Install dependencies
```bash
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv stress -y
mkdir autoscale-project && cd autoscale-project
python3 -m venv myenv
source myenv/bin/activate
```

### Step 2: Install gcloud CLI
```bash
sudo snap install google-cloud-cli --classic
gcloud auth login --no-launch-browser
gcloud config set project auto-scale-vm-project
gcloud config set compute/zone asia-south2-a
```

### Step 3: Run the demo
```bash
# Terminal 1 — start stress to simulate high CPU
stress --cpu 2 &

# Terminal 2 — run monitor
python3 monitor.py
```

### Step 4: Watch auto-scaling trigger
When CPU > 70%, the monitor automatically runs:
```
gcloud compute instances create autoscale-vm-XXXX \
  --zone=asia-south2-a \
  --machine-type=e2-micro \
  --image-family=ubuntu-2204-lts \
  --image-project=ubuntu-os-cloud \
  --tags=http-server \
  --metadata-from-file=startup-script=startup.sh
```

### Step 5: Access the deployed app
```
http://<external-ip>
```

### Step 6: Cleanup
```bash
gcloud compute instances delete autoscale-vm-XXXX \
  --zone=asia-south2-a --quiet
```

